00:24:28.424 --> 00:24:29.715
JAY CHANDRASEKHAR: That scene--

00:24:34.070 --> 00:24:39.110
we were writing "Super
Troopers" and we were in--

00:24:39.110 --> 00:24:44.480
the five of us were sleeping
in a motel in Burbank

00:24:44.480 --> 00:24:46.800
because we didn't
have much cash.

00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:49.250
And we were up
smoking and joking

00:24:49.250 --> 00:24:51.110
and it was about
4:30 in the morning.

00:24:51.110 --> 00:24:54.221
And I have a bad left ear from
like ear infections as a kid

00:24:54.221 --> 00:24:54.720
from--

00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:56.845
I used to swim in this lake
that was kind of dirty.

00:24:59.550 --> 00:25:02.770
And so the ear's not that great.

00:25:02.770 --> 00:25:05.600
And I heard somebody say
something now and I say,

00:25:05.600 --> 00:25:06.980
did you say meow?

00:25:06.980 --> 00:25:10.190
And then for the next hour
we riffed on sentences

00:25:10.190 --> 00:25:13.220
with meow replacing now.

00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:14.750
And then we just went to bed.

00:25:14.750 --> 00:25:19.580
And somebody wrote on a
napkin now equals meow.

00:25:19.580 --> 00:25:22.490
And three weeks later, we
were in a writing meeting

00:25:22.490 --> 00:25:25.221
and someone's like-- we were
trying to think of a pullover.

00:25:25.221 --> 00:25:25.970
What could you do?

00:25:25.970 --> 00:25:27.595
And someone's like,
remember that thing

00:25:27.595 --> 00:25:29.280
we did where the
meow is the now?

00:25:29.280 --> 00:25:30.810
And we're like, oh, yeah.

00:25:30.810 --> 00:25:32.800
And so we wrote up
that little scene.

00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:36.050
And we were reading it.

00:25:36.050 --> 00:25:38.330
Once we finished the
movie, we were reading it.

00:25:38.330 --> 00:25:45.400
And at one point I was
going to be the meow guy.

00:25:45.400 --> 00:25:47.910
I was going to be in that scene.

00:25:47.910 --> 00:25:51.470
But the movie takes
place in Vermont.

00:25:51.470 --> 00:25:54.440
And you're like, OK.

00:25:54.440 --> 00:25:56.240
The problem with the
scene was we read it

00:25:56.240 --> 00:26:01.280
without a Southern accent
and it wasn't that funny.

00:26:01.280 --> 00:26:03.216
It just didn't land.

00:26:03.216 --> 00:26:05.090
And then when we put a
Southern accent on it,

00:26:05.090 --> 00:26:05.990
it was really funny.

00:26:05.990 --> 00:26:12.500
And I'm like, I said I could buy
a white Southerner in Vermont,

00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:13.220
I could buy that.

00:26:13.220 --> 00:26:16.640
But like an Indian guy with
a southern accent in Vermont,

00:26:16.640 --> 00:26:18.680
I was like, I just don't buy it.

00:26:18.680 --> 00:26:23.882
So I had Paul do it,
and, you know, lucky him.

00:26:23.882 --> 00:26:25.340
ALLAN WEINBERGER:
