00:28:51.640 --> 00:28:55.270
JAY CHANDRASEKHAR: I have a
lot to say about that scene.

00:28:55.270 --> 00:28:58.180
The kid who played the
Dimpus Burger Guy is a guy

00:28:58.180 --> 00:28:59.950
named Charlie Finn.

00:28:59.950 --> 00:29:06.010
And I discovered him on
the streets of Hollywood.

00:29:06.010 --> 00:29:08.440
I went to the Improv
Olympic in Hollywood

00:29:08.440 --> 00:29:13.300
looking for guys that age to put
into a pilot we were shooting.

00:29:13.300 --> 00:29:15.630
And I didn't really see
anybody perform that day.

00:29:15.630 --> 00:29:17.620
But then I went outside
and I saw this guy

00:29:17.620 --> 00:29:20.800
smoking a cigarette, and
he's like meh, meh, meh.

00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:22.289
He was just talking real funny.

00:29:22.289 --> 00:29:24.580
And I went up to him, and I
was like, are you an actor?

00:29:24.580 --> 00:29:27.160
And he goes, I guess.

00:29:27.160 --> 00:29:30.060
And I was like, you want to
audition for an NBC pilot?

00:29:30.060 --> 00:29:32.590
He goes, OK.

00:29:32.590 --> 00:29:34.900
And he'd never been
on an audition.

00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:37.460
He was just a funny guy
who moved out to Hollywood.

00:29:37.460 --> 00:29:39.460
He was in the Improv Olympic.

00:29:39.460 --> 00:29:42.880
And we got him onto this NBC
show and he was hilarious.

00:29:42.880 --> 00:29:45.480
And so we cast him in this role.

00:29:45.480 --> 00:29:48.700
And it's probably my favorite
performance in the movie.

00:29:48.700 --> 00:29:49.600
I love this guy.

00:29:53.010 --> 00:29:55.970
So the origin of
this scene was--

00:29:55.970 --> 00:30:00.816
we used to go to
Burger King in our--

00:30:00.816 --> 00:30:01.440
Let me go back.

00:30:01.440 --> 00:30:02.815
Let me talk about
something else.

00:30:02.815 --> 00:30:07.350
So McDonald's invented
the notion of supersizing.

00:30:07.350 --> 00:30:09.027
I think it was while
we were in college.

00:30:09.027 --> 00:30:10.860
They used to have just
small, medium, large.

00:30:10.860 --> 00:30:12.680
Then they invented
the supersized.

00:30:12.680 --> 00:30:15.330
And their employees
were instructed

00:30:15.330 --> 00:30:21.380
to badger the customers
until they upsold this thing.

00:30:21.380 --> 00:30:24.420
And so you'd go in, you're
like, I'll have a large.

00:30:24.420 --> 00:30:26.790
They're like, you
want to supersize it

00:30:26.790 --> 00:30:27.630
for a quarter more?

00:30:27.630 --> 00:30:28.374
And I'm like, no.

00:30:28.374 --> 00:30:29.790
They're like, it's
just a quarter.

00:30:29.790 --> 00:30:30.750
I'm like, no.

00:30:30.750 --> 00:30:32.249
They're like, it's
just a quarter.

00:30:32.249 --> 00:30:33.540
I mean, really, just a quarter?

00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:36.660
And I became so
frustrated by it that we

00:30:36.660 --> 00:30:39.570
wrote that scene into that.

00:30:39.570 --> 00:30:43.230
And then the liter--

00:30:43.230 --> 00:30:46.470
the Burger King in
our town was managed

00:30:46.470 --> 00:30:51.390
by a guy who I'm certain
was a Canadian because he

00:30:51.390 --> 00:30:53.760
had small, medium, and liter.

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:55.260
He did not have a large.

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:59.370
And we would roll in, hungover
on a Saturday afternoon,

00:30:59.370 --> 00:31:01.500
and buy liters of iced tea.

00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:03.430
But I'm an American.

00:31:03.430 --> 00:31:04.700
I want a large iced tea.

00:31:04.700 --> 00:31:06.330
I do not want a liter.

00:31:06.330 --> 00:31:08.570
I do not go metric.

00:31:08.570 --> 00:31:10.620
And so we'd go in and we'd say--

00:31:10.620 --> 00:31:13.920
I'd say, give me a large
iced tea or a large Coke.

00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:17.100
And he instructed his workers
to say, we don't have larges,

00:31:17.100 --> 00:31:18.510
we only have liters.

00:31:18.510 --> 00:31:22.530
And so I'd sit there at
the speaker and be like,

00:31:22.530 --> 00:31:23.459
give me a large.

00:31:23.459 --> 00:31:25.500
And he's like, we don't
have large, just a liter.

00:31:25.500 --> 00:31:27.150
And we would go at it.

00:31:27.150 --> 00:31:29.160
And finally I'm like,
fine, give me a liter.

00:31:29.160 --> 00:31:32.710
And this Canadian
bastard just won this--

00:31:32.710 --> 00:31:33.210
he won.

00:31:33.210 --> 00:31:33.810
He won.

00:31:33.810 --> 00:31:35.520
And we got him back.

00:31:39.334 --> 00:31:40.500
ALLAN WEINBERGER: All right.

00:31:40.500 --> 00:31:41.708
Thank you very much for that.

